Authorities were investigating a police shooting in South Los Angeles on Tuesday night. Officers were called around 7 p.m. to a report of a man with a gun near East Martin Luther King Jr. and South Avalon boulevards, said Officer Drake Madison, a Los Angeles Police Department spokesman. Madison confirmed at least one officer opened fire. He could not confirm whether the man was shot by police, but he said there was a medical transport from the scene. As of shortly before 11 p.m., Madison could not provide further information about the shooting or what led up to it. 